    "sections": {
        "description": "<p>This plugin adds a block to the editor allowing you to easily show and hide content using the HTML <code>details</code> and <code>summary</code> elements. It can be used for content such as FAQs or accordions.</p>\n<p>It uses built-in browser functionality and doesn&#8217;t rely on any JavaScript. Styling is customizable via the editor or custom CSS.</p>\n",
        "installation": "<ol>\n<li>Upload the plugin files to the <code>/wp-content/plugins/wp-details-block</code> directory, or install the plugin through the WordPress plugins screen directly.</li>\n<li>Activate the plugin through the &#8216;Plugins&#8217; screen in WordPress</li>\n<li>Start adding content.</li>\n</ol>\n",
        "faq": "\n<dt id='how%20do%20i%20customize%20the%20styling%3F'>\nHow do I customize the styling?\n</h4>\n<p>\n<p>The wrapper <code>&lt;details&gt;</code> element has the class <code>.wp-block-bm-wp-details-container</code> that you can use to target it and adjust styling as needed.</p>\n<p>The <code>&lt;summary&gt;</code> element has the class <code>.wp-block-bm-wp-details-block</code>.</p>\n</p>\n<dt id='where%20can%20i%20learn%20more%20about%20browser%20support%3F'>\nWhere can I learn more about browser support?\n</h4>\n<p>\n<p>Details is supported in most major browsers (Chrome, Firefox, and Safari). Caniuse.com has a breakdown of browser support for <a href=\"https://caniuse.com/details\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">the details element</a>.</p>\n</p>\n\n",
        "changelog": "<h4>1.0</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Initial release</li>\n</ul>\n"
    },
